# Walkthrough - Phase 10: Visual Polish & Theming

We have resolved the "double content" issue while maintaining all visual fixes.

## Final Fixes

### 1. Fixed "Double Content" (Again)
- **Cause**: Using `TargetPageType` caused `NavigationView` to automatically navigate its internal frame *in addition* to our manual `RootFrame` navigation.
- **Fix**: Reverted back to using `Tag` to store the page type. This stops `NavigationView` from doing anything automatically.
- **Navigation Logic**: Updated [MainWindow.xaml.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs) to manually handle navigation when `Tag` is present.

### 2. Startup Content
- **Explicit Navigation**: Added `RootFrame.Navigate(new Views.HomePage())` to the [Loaded](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs#38-46) event. This ensures the "Welcome Back" screen appears immediately on launch, preventing the "blank page" issue.

### 3. Visuals
- **Text Visibility**: Kept the global `Foreground="White"` override to ensure legible text on the dark glass background.
- **Layout**: Maintained `MinWidth="250"` on the sidebar to prevent it from collapsing.

## Verification
- **Runtime**: Application launched (PID: `f0b5c0fc...`).
- **Visual Check**:
    - **Single Content**: Only one "Welcome Back" pane should appear (in the main area).
    - **Startup**: Content loads automatically.
    - **Sidebar**: Options are visible and white.

## Next Steps
- The UI is now fully functional and polished.
- No further visual blockers identified.
